Create Thingworx IoT Gateway
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Data-Collector" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Kepware".
4
Move to "Create IoT Gateway".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Select a Kepware Channel and click on it to expand its menu.
6
Choose "Thingworx".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Open the "Local Things". If you have already added machine serial numbers in the
"Data Collector -> Kepware -> Local Thing" tab, you can select them automatically.
8
Select the "Custom Endpoint" checkbox if you want to use a new custom Local
Thing, that has not been already added to the "Data Collector -> Kepware -> Local
Thing" tab.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Enter the custom local thing name in the "Local Thing" field if you selected custom
endpoint.
10
Click the "Create" button if you want to create an IoT Gateway without selecting
specifics tags, by default they are all selected.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Select the "Choose tags" checkbox if you want to choose specific tags.
12
Then click the "Create" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Click on the little "arrow" on the left to expand the folder and tick all the tags (or
folders) you want to use.
14
Click the "greater than" button between "Channel" and "IoT Gateway", after you
finished choosing the tags (or folders) you need.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
15
Click the "Create IoT Gateway" button to complete the operation.
16
You can now click on the "Close" button.
